Some ideas: If you bid a suit at the 1-level over a double, it is a 1 round force, but it shows less than 10 HCP.  
If your partner opens 1 of a Major and RHO doubles, then 2NT = a limit raise or better.  
If pard opens 1 of a minor, and you have 10+ HCP, redouble to show that your side has the balance of strength.  
2@s would be a weak bid, showing this hand minus the @DAK.  
In standard bidding (SA or 2 over 1), 1@D (x) 2@h (or 2@s) is a weak bid with not much defense.|
