at|WestElsdon:  So XX?
mitche:  Yes, XX.  After the XX, West will get another chance, and with spades (also known as the Boss suit) West will 
have the chance to bid it at the same level  as anything N/S would say.  
So a sample auction might be:
1@d (X) XX (2@h)/pass, pass, 2@s pass/ 3@s.  And if N/S compete to the 3 level, E/W can decide whether to double or 
bid 3@s or 4@s and unless N/S get the clubs going early, E/W will make 4@s.   
One more point: when West bids 2@s freely, East might wish to raise to 3@s anyway.|
