at|mitche:  Something to think about, folks: after South passes, a NT bid cannot possibly be natural, 
so it must be some kind of takeout.
And if E/W bid and raise spades, North cannot have more than 2 spades, maybe less. 
(South knows this because he can account for at least 10 spades on the bidding and his hand.)
